00:30:25.110 --> 00:30:28.890
So he shared with me
this very high-level view

00:30:28.890 --> 00:30:33.930
of how their product managers,
designers, and engineers work

00:30:33.930 --> 00:30:39.390
together to create their app.

00:30:39.390 --> 00:30:43.060
And I think it encapsulates
well the principles at work.

00:30:43.060 --> 00:30:45.890
So it applies data.

00:30:45.890 --> 00:30:48.170
But it doesn't rely
on data entirely.

00:30:48.170 --> 00:30:50.790
The feedback is
also qualitative.

00:30:50.790 --> 00:30:53.490
And it also means that
growth is never done.

00:30:53.490 --> 00:30:55.520
So you have these
continuous feedback loops

00:30:55.520 --> 00:30:57.780
of how they do development.

00:30:57.780 --> 00:31:01.220
Another key thing I think that
you need to remind yourself

00:31:01.220 --> 00:31:04.800
is that growth strategy
is very cross-functional.

00:31:04.800 --> 00:31:06.810
It's a cross-functional
endeavor.

00:31:06.810 --> 00:31:09.300
And so the quality
of your execution

00:31:09.300 --> 00:31:12.030
will depend on assembling
the right skill

00:31:12.030 --> 00:31:17.310
set and the right people in your
team to actually execute well.

00:31:17.310 --> 00:31:20.520
So I hope that,
as I said before,

00:31:20.520 --> 00:31:24.120
you chat to other developers
here and really try

00:31:24.120 --> 00:31:29.010
to get to the bottom of how
other people in the industry

00:31:29.010 --> 00:31:32.310
are set up to drive growth.

00:31:32.310 --> 00:31:34.400
One last thing I
want to emphasize

00:31:34.400 --> 00:31:38.790
is the importance of
continuously tracking

00:31:38.790 --> 00:31:40.500
your progress, whether
you use a growth

00:31:40.500 --> 00:31:42.710
scorecard or some other device.

00:31:42.710 --> 00:31:46.860
It's important with
successful growth strategy

00:31:46.860 --> 00:31:50.040
to flag problems
early on so that you

00:31:50.040 --> 00:31:52.530
know whether the
investments you're making

00:31:52.530 --> 00:31:55.860
are bringing you closer
to the goals you've

00:31:55.860 --> 00:31:57.700
stated for your KPIs.

00:31:57.700 --> 00:32:01.670
And also, re-evaluate your
growth strategy continuously

00:32:01.670 --> 00:32:05.150
as internal and
external factors change.

00:32:05.150 --> 00:32:09.010
So that was the first
part of this presentation.

00:32:09.010 --> 00:32:10.970
Before I call on Andy,
I just want to give you

00:32:10.970 --> 00:32:12.380
a very quick summary.

00:32:12.380 --> 00:32:15.960
So first we looked at how
complex the whole topic

00:32:15.960 --> 00:32:17.070
of growth is.

00:32:17.070 --> 00:32:20.210
But then we luckily introduced
a very simple tool, the growth

00:32:20.210 --> 00:32:22.770
framework, to deal with this.

00:32:22.770 --> 00:32:25.830
And the first step is to look
at your high-level business

00:32:25.830 --> 00:32:28.350
objectives to define
what growth means

00:32:28.350 --> 00:32:30.140
for you and for your business.

00:32:30.140 --> 00:32:32.430
And then, really focus
only on the techniques

00:32:32.430 --> 00:32:35.080
that makes sense for you--
the tactics and the tools

00:32:35.080 --> 00:32:36.570
that make sense for you.

00:32:36.570 --> 00:32:39.960
And importantly, be
able to track the impact

00:32:39.960 --> 00:32:41.180
that you're having.

00:32:41.180 --> 00:32:43.680
Also, define really
good KPIs for you

00:32:43.680 --> 00:32:46.060
that are measurable
and actionable.

00:32:46.060 --> 00:32:50.490
And have some sort of way
of making sure you visualize

00:32:50.490 --> 00:32:51.890
whether you're on track.

00:32:51.890 --> 00:32:55.920
And then, continuously look
at the data as it comes in.

00:32:55.920 --> 00:32:58.370
And track your progress to
make sure you're on track.

00:32:58.370 --> 00:33:02.360
And make changes as necessary.

00:33:02.360 --> 00:33:05.580
Now Marie and I-- we
covered the framework.

00:33:05.580 --> 00:33:07.190
We gave you some examples.

